          "date": "2012-07-13 09:45:53.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Yu Jian",
          "email": "yujian@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2012-07-14 07:38:07.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-1129 obdfilter: handle race condition of recreating objects",
        "message": "LU-1129 obdfilter: handle race condition of recreating objects\n\nDuring OST recovery, a race can happen while handling replayed\nOST_WRITE request during the MDS->OST orphan recovery period to\nrecreate missing objects, which can trigger ASSERTION(diff >= 0)\nfailure.\n\nThis patch handles the above issue by adding obd->obd_recovering\ninto the assertion to check whether the OST is in recovery or not.\nIf it's in recovery and diff < 0, then no assertion failure occurs,\nthe object has been recreated. If the OST is not in recovery and\ndiff < 0, then the assertion failure occurs.\n\nSigned-off-by: Yu Jian <yujian@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: If486bc8221cf4b9d53b6de53e8ec14a4f3174b45\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
